      "skill_original": "---\nname: openspec-archive-change\ndescription: Archive a completed change in the experimental workflow. Use when the user wants to finalize and archive a change after implementation is complete.\nlicense: MIT\ncompatibility: Requires openspec CLI.\nmetadata:\n  author: openspec\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  generatedBy: \"1.4.1\"\n---\n\nArchive a completed change in the experimental workflow.\n\n**Input**: Optionally specify a change name. If omitted, check if it can be inferred from conversation context. If vague or ambiguous you MUST prompt for available changes.\n\n**Steps**\n\n1. **If no change name provided, prompt for selection**\n\n   Run `openspec list --json` to get available changes. Use the **AskUserQuestion tool** to let the user select.\n\n   Show only active changes (not already archived).\n   Include the schema used for each change if available.\n\n   **IMPORTANT**: Do NOT guess or auto-select a change. Always let the user choose.\n\n2. **Check artifact completion status**\n\n   Run `openspec status --change \"<name>\" --json` to check artifact completion.\n\n   Parse the JSON to understand:\n   - `schemaName`: The workflow being used\n   - `planningHome`, `changeRoot`, `artifactPaths`, and `actionContext`: path and scope context\n   - `artifacts`: List of artifacts with their status (`done` or other)\n\n   If status reports `actionContext.mode: \"workspace-planning\"`, explain that workspace archive is not supported in this slice and STOP. Do not move workspace changes into repo-local archives or edit linked repos.\n\n   **If any artifacts are not `done`:**\n   - Display warning listing incomplete artifacts\n   - Use **AskUserQuestion tool** to confirm user wants to proceed\n   - Proceed if user confirms\n\n3. **Check task completion status**\n\n   Read the tasks file (typically `tasks.md`) to check for incomplete tasks.\n\n   Count tasks marked with `- [ ]` (incomplete) vs `- [x]` (complete).\n\n   **If incomplete tasks found:**\n   - Display warning showing count of incomplete tasks\n   - Use **AskUserQuestion tool** to confirm user wants to proceed\n   - Proceed if user confirms\n\n   **If no tasks file exists:** Proceed without task-related warning.\n\n4. **Assess delta spec sync state**\n\n   Use `artifactPaths.specs.existingOutputPaths` from status JSON to check for delta specs. If none exist, proceed without sync prompt.\n\n   **If delta specs exist:**\n   - Compare each delta spec with its corresponding main spec at `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md`\n   - Determine what changes would be applied (adds, modifications, removals, renames)\n   - Show a combined summary before prompting\n\n   **Prompt options:**\n   - If changes needed: \"Sync now (recommended)\", \"Archive without syncing\"\n   - If already synced: \"Archive now\", \"Sync anyway\", \"Cancel\"\n\n   If user chooses sync, use Task tool (subagent_type: \"general-purpose\", prompt: \"Use Skill tool to invoke openspec-sync-specs for change '<name>'. Delta spec analysis: <include the analyzed delta spec summary>\"). Proceed to archive regardless of choice.\n\n5. **Perform the archive**\n\n   Create an `archive` directory under `planningHome.changesDir` if it doesn't exist:\n   ```bash\n   mkdir -p \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive\"\n   ```\n\n   Generate target name using current date: `YYYY-MM-DD-<change-name>`\n\n   **Check if target already exists:**\n   - If yes: Fail with error, suggest renaming existing archive or using different date\n   - If no: Move `changeRoot` to the archive directory\n\n   ```bash\n   mv \"<changeRoot>\" \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>\"\n   ```\n\n6. **Display summary**\n\n   Show archive completion summary including:\n   - Change name\n   - Schema that was used\n   - Archive location\n   - Whether specs were synced (if applicable)\n   - Note about any warnings (incomplete artifacts/tasks)\n\n**Output On Success**\n\n```\n## Archive Complete\n\n**Change:** <change-name>\n**Schema:** <schema-name>\n**Archived to:** the archive path derived from `planningHome.changesDir`/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>/\n**Specs:** ✓ Synced to main specs (or \"No delta specs\" or \"Sync skipped\")\n\nAll artifacts complete. All tasks complete.\n```\n\n**Guardrails**\n- Always prompt for change selection if not provided\n- Use artifact graph (openspec status --json) for completion checking\n- Don't block archive on warnings - just inform and confirm\n- Preserve .openspec.yaml when moving to archive (it moves with the directory)\n- Show clear summary of what happened\n- If sync is requested, use openspec-sync-specs approach (agent-driven)\n- If delta specs exist, always run the sync assessment and show the combined summary before prompting",
      "skill_otimizada": "---\nname: openspec-archive-change\ndescription: Archive a completed change in the experimental workflow. Use when the user wants to finalize and archive a change after implementation is complete.\nlicense: MIT\ncompatibility: Requires openspec CLI.\nmetadata:\n  author: openspec\n  version: \"1.1\"\n  generatedBy: \"1.4.1\"\n---\n\nArchive a completed change in the experimental workflow with deterministic, unambiguous behavior for every edge case.\n\n**Input**: Optionally specify a change name. If omitted, check if it can be inferred from conversation context. If vague or ambiguous you MUST prompt for available changes.\n\n---\n\n## Steps\n\n### 1. Resolve the change name\n\n**Se** um nome de change foi fornecido explicitamente pelo usuário (ex.: `archive \"add-auth-module\"`), **então** use-o diretamente e pule para o passo 2.\n\n**Se** nenhum nome foi fornecido, **então** tente inferir do contexto da conversa. Regras de inferência:\n- Se a conversa atual tratou de exatamente UMA change ativa, use-a.\n- Se houver ambiguidade (zero ou múltiplas candidates), NÃO adivinhe.\n\n**Se** houver ambiguidade, **então** execute `openspec list --json` e use a ferramenta **AskUserQuestion** para seleção.\n\n**Exemplo de exibição da lista** (INPUT→OUTPUT):\n\n```\nINPUT: openspec list --json\nOUTPUT:\n{\n  \"changes\": [\n    { \"name\": \"add-auth-module\", \"status\": \"active\", \"schemaName\": \"rfc-light\" },\n    { \"name\": \"refactor-db-layer\", \"status\": \"active\", \"schemaName\": \"rfc-heavy\" },\n    { \"name\": \"fix-typos\", \"status\": \"archived\", \"schemaName\": \"rfc-light\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nApresente ao usuário SOMENTE as changes com `status: \"active\"`. Exemplo de prompt:\n\n```\nWhich change would you like to archive?\n- add-auth-module (schema: rfc-light)\n- refactor-db-layer (schema: rfc-heavy)\n```\n\n**Edge case**: Se `openspec list --json` retornar uma lista vazia ou erro, exiba: \"No active changes found. Nothing to archive.\" e ENCERRE.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Check artifact completion status\n\nExecute:\n\n```bash\nopenspec status --change \"<name>\" --json\n```\n\n**Campos críticos do JSON a interpretar**:\n- `schemaName`: workflow usado.\n- `planningHome.changesDir`: diretório base onde ficará o `archive/`.\n- `changeRoot`: caminho completo da change a ser movida.\n- `artifactPaths.specs.existingOutputPaths`: lista de delta specs (usado no passo 4).\n- `actionContext.mode`: modo de operação.\n\n**Regra crítica — workspace-planning**:\n\n**Se** `actionContext.mode === \"workspace-planning\"`, **então** exiba a mensagem exata abaixo e ENCERRE imediatamente:\n\n```\n⚠️ Workspace archive not supported in this slice.\n\nThis change is in workspace-planning mode and cannot be archived into\nrepo-local archives. Workspace changes must not be moved into linked repos.\n```\n\n**Regra — artifacts incompletos**:\n\nItere sobre `artifacts[]`. Conte quantos têm `status !== \"done\"`.\n\n**Se** algum artifact não estiver `done`, **então** exiba o warning no formato:\n\n```\n⚠️ Incomplete Artifacts Detected\n\nThe following artifacts are not marked as done:\n  • <artifact-name-1> — status: <status>\n  • <artifact-name-2> — status: <status>\n\nYou can still archive, but incomplete work will be preserved as-is.\n```\n\nUse **AskUserQuestion** com opções:\n- \"Proceed with archive anyway\"\n- \"Cancel\"\n\n**Se** o usuário cancelar, **então** ENCERRE sem mover nada.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Check task completion status\n\nLocalize o arquivo de tasks (geralmente `tasks.md` dentro do `changeRoot`).\n\n**Se** o arquivo não existir, **então** pule este passo sem warning (proceda ao passo 4).\n\n**Se** o arquivo existir, **então** conte linhas:\n- `- [ ]` = incomplete\n- `- [x]` = complete\n\n**Exemplo de contagem** (INPUT→OUTPUT):\n\n```\nINPUT (tasks.md):\n- [x] Create spec for auth module\n- [x] Implement login endpoint\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n- [ ] Update documentation\n\nOUTPUT: 2 complete, 2 incomplete\n```\n\n**Se** houver tasks incompletas, **então** exiba:\n\n```\n⚠️ Incomplete Tasks: 2 of 4\n\nIncomplete tasks:\n  • Add integration tests\n  • Update documentation\n\nArchiving will preserve these as incomplete permanently.\n```\n\nUse **AskUserQuestion** com:\n- \"Proceed with archive anyway\"\n- \"Cancel\"\n\n---\n\n### 4. Assess delta spec sync state\n\nUse `artifactPaths.specs.existingOutputPaths` do JSON do passo 2.\n\n**Se** a lista estiver vazia, **então** pule a sincronização (nenhum delta spec existe). Proceda ao passo 5 marcando `specs: \"No delta specs\"`.\n\n**Se** houver delta specs, **então** para cada delta spec:\n1. Leia o delta spec em `<changeRoot>/specs/<capability>/spec.md`.\n2. Leia o spec principal correspondente em `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md`.\n3. Determine as mudanças: ADICIONADOS, MODIFICADOS, REMOVIDOS, RENOMEADOS.\n\n**Exemplo de resumo combinado** a apresentar:\n\n```\n📋 Delta Spec Sync Analysis\n\nCapability: auth\n  + ADDED: `loginRateLimit` field in config schema\n  ~ MODIFIED: `authenticate()` signature (added `options` param)\n  - REMOVED: deprecated `legacyAuth` flag\n  ↔ RENAMED: `userToken` → `sessionToken`\n\nCapability: database\n  + ADDED: `connectionPool` section\n```\n\n**Prompt de sincronização** (use **AskUserQuestion**):\n\n**Se** mudanças são necessárias (delta ≠ main):\n- \"Sync now (recommended)\" — aplica deltas ao spec principal\n- \"Archive without syncing\"\n\n**Se** já está sincronizado (delta == main):\n- \"Archive now\"\n- \"Sync anyway\"\n- \"Cancel\"\n\n**Regra de execução de sync**:\n\n**Se** o usuário escolher sincronizar, **então** invoque a ferramenta **Task** com:\n- `subagent_type`: `\"general-purpose\"`\n- `prompt`: `\"Use Skill tool to invoke openspec-sync-specs for change '<name>'. Delta spec analysis: <cole o resumo do passo acima>\"`\n\nIndependentemente da escolha (sync ou skip), **proceda ao passo 5** (a menos que o usuário tenha escolhido \"Cancel\").\n\n---\n\n### 5. Perform the archive\n\n**5a. Crie o diretório de archive**:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive\"\n```\n\n**5b. Gere o nome do target** usando a data atual:\n\n```\nTARGET = <planningHome.changesDir>/archive/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<change-name>\n```\n\n**Exemplo**: Se hoje é 2025-01-15 e a change é `add-auth-module`:\n```\n/home/user/project/.openspec/changes/archive/2025-01-15-add-auth-module\n```\n\n**5c. Verifique colisão de nome**:\n\n**Se** o target já existir, **então** FALHE com:\n\n```\n❌ Archive target already exists: <TARGET>\n\nOptions:\n  1. Rename the existing archive folder manually.\n  2. Use a different date suffix (e.g., append -v2).\n  3. Remove the existing archive if it's a duplicate.\n```\n\n**Se** não existir, **então** mova:\n\n```bash\nmv \"<changeRoot>\" \"<TARGET>\"\n```\n\n**Edge case — .openspec.yaml**: O arquivo `.openspec.yaml` deve ser preservado automaticamente, pois ele se move junto com o diretório. Não edite nem remova este arquivo.\n\n**Edge case — path relativo vs absoluto**: Sempre use caminhos absolutos ao executar `mv`. Se `planningHome.changesDir` for relativo, resolva para absoluto antes de executar.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Display summary\n\nExiba obrigatoriamente todos os campos abaixo. Use exatamente este template:\n\n```\n## Archive Complete\n\n**Change:** <change-name>\n**Schema:** <schema-name>\n**Archived to:** <absolute-archive-path>\n**Specs:** ✓ Synced to main specs | \"No delta specs\" | \"Sync skipped\"\n**Artifacts:** <N>/<total> complete\n**Tasks:** <N>/<total> complete\n\n⚠️ Warnings: <list any, or \"None\">\n```\n\n**Exemplo de output real**:\n\n```\n## Archive Complete\n\n**Change:** add-auth-module\n**Schema:** rfc-light\n**Archived to:** /home/user/project/.openspec/changes/archive/2025-01-15-add-auth-module\n**Specs:** ✓ Synced to main specs\n**Artifacts:** 4/5 complete\n**Tasks:** 6/8 complete\n\n⚠️ Warnings:\n  • Artifact \"integration-tests\" not done\n  • 2 tasks incomplete: Add integration tests, Update documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n## Guardrails (Quick Reference)\n\n| Situação | Ação Exata |\n|---|---|\n| Nome não fornecido e contexto ambíguo | Prompt com `AskUserQuestion` listando apenas changes ativas |\n| `actionContext.mode === \"workspace-planning\"` | Exibir mensagem de bloqueio e ENCERRAR |\n| Artifact com `status !== \"done\"` | Warning + confirmar com usuário + prosseguir se confirmado |\n| Tasks file ausente | Prosseguir sem warning de tasks |\n| Tasks incompletas (>0) | Warning + confirmar + prosseguir se confirmado |\n| Delta specs existem | Sempre analisar e mostrar resumo combinado antes de prompt |\n| Delta specs ausentes | Pular sync, marcar `\"No delta specs\"` |\n| Target de archive já existe | FALHAR com mensagem de resolução |\n| Usuário escolhe \"Cancel\" em qualquer prompt | ENCERRAR sem mover nada |\n| `.openspec.yaml` | Preservar (move com o diretório, não editar) |\n| Path relativo em `mv` | Resolver para absoluto antes de executar |\n\n---\n\n## Anti-Patterns (NUNCA faça)\n\n- **NUNCA** adivinhe ou auto-selecione uma change sem confirmação explícita do usuário.\n- **NUNCA** mova uma change de workspace-planning para archive repo-local.\n- **NUNCA** bloqueie o archive por warnings — apenas informe e confirme.\n- **NUNCA** edite o conteúdo do `.openspec.yaml` durante o archive.\n- **NUNCA** execute `mv` sem antes verificar se o target já existe.\n- **NUNCA** pule a análise de delta specs quando elas existirem — sempre mostre o resumo combinado.",
      "regras_adicionais": "Preservar todas as regras comportamentais anteriores.",
      "manteve_regras_criticas": "True",
      "nota_clareza": "100",
      "nota_formatacao": "100",
