      "nota_acionabilidade": "100",
      "nota_anti_fragilidade": "100",
      "feedback_detalhado": "A skill otimizada é estruturalmente muito superior à original. Ela converte instruções narrativas em um fluxo de trabalho determinístico, baseado em lógica condicional (Se... Então...), eliminando ambiguidades. \n\n**Pontos Fortes:**\n1. **Clareza e Ação:** O uso de exemplos práticos de INPUT/OUTPUT, blocos de código para mensagens exatas e a especificação de comandos bash garantem que um agente de IA saberá exatamente o que fazer em cada etapa.\n2. **Formatação:** Uso excelente de Markdown, com títulos hierárquicos, tabelas de referência rápida e listas que previnem o efeito 'lost in the middle'.\n3. **Anti-fragilidade:** A inclusão de uma seção 'Anti-Patterns' e o tratamento de edge cases (como caminhos relativos, colisão de nomes, listas vazias e escolha explícita de 'Cancel' em menus) tornam a instrução altamente resistente a falhas.\n\n**Regras Críticas:** Todas as regras da original e as adicionais foram rigorosamente integradas, muitas vezes aprimoradas com mensagens de erro explícitas para o usuário."
    },
    {
      "augmented": true,
      "skill_original": "---\nname: openspec-archive-change\ndescription: Archive a completed change in the experimental workflow. Use when the user wants to finalize and archive a change after implementation is complete.\nlicense: MIT\ncompatibility: Requires openspec CLI.\nmetadata:\n  author: openspec\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  generatedBy: \"1.4.1\"\n---\n\nArchive a completed change in the experimental workflow.\n\n**Input**: Optionally specify a change name. If omitted, check if it can be inferred from conversation context. If vague or ambiguous you MUST prompt for available changes.\n\n**Steps**\n\n1. **If no change name provided, prompt for selection**\n\n   Run `openspec list --json` to get available changes. Use the **AskUserQuestion tool** to let the user select.\n\n   Show only active changes (not already archived).\n   Include the schema used for each change if available.\n\n   **IMPORTANT**: Do NOT guess or auto-select a change. Always let the user choose.\n\n2. **Check artifact completion status**\n\n   Run `openspec status --change \"<name>\" --json` to check artifact completion.\n\n   Parse the JSON to understand:\n   - `schemaName`: The workflow being used\n   - `planningHome`, `changeRoot`, `artifactPaths`, and `actionContext`: path and scope context\n   - `artifacts`: List of artifacts with their status (`done` or other)\n\n   If status reports `actionContext.mode: \"workspace-planning\"`, explain that workspace archive is not supported in this slice and STOP. Do not move workspace changes into repo-local archives or edit linked repos.\n\n   **If any artifacts are not `done`:**\n   - Display warning listing incomplete artifacts\n   - Use **AskUserQuestion tool** to confirm user wants to proceed\n   - Proceed if user confirms\n\n3. **Check task completion status**\n\n   Read the tasks file (typically `tasks.md`) to check for incomplete tasks.\n\n   Count tasks marked with `- [ ]` (incomplete) vs `- [x]` (complete).\n\n   **If incomplete tasks found:**\n   - Display warning showing count of incomplete tasks\n   - Use **AskUserQuestion tool** to confirm user wants to proceed\n   - Proceed if user confirms\n\n   **If no tasks file exists:** Proceed without task-related warning.\n\n4. **Assess delta spec sync state**\n\n   Use `artifactPaths.specs.existingOutputPaths` from status JSON to check for delta specs. If none exist, proceed without sync prompt.\n\n   **If delta specs exist:**\n   - Compare each delta spec with its corresponding main spec at `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md`\n   - Determine what changes would be applied (adds, modifications, removals, renames)\n   - Show a combined summary before prompting\n\n   **Prompt options:**\n   - If changes needed: \"Sync now (recommended)\", \"Archive without syncing\"\n   - If already synced: \"Archive now\", \"Sync anyway\", \"Cancel\"\n\n   If user chooses sync, use Task tool (subagent_type: \"general-purpose\", prompt: \"Use Skill tool to invoke openspec-sync-specs for change '<name>'. Delta spec analysis: <include the analyzed delta spec summary>\"). Proceed to archive regardless of choice.\n\n5. **Perform the archive**\n\n   Create an `archive` directory under `planningHome.changesDir` if it doesn't exist:\n   ```bash\n   mkdir -p \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive\"\n   ```\n\n   Generate target name using current date: `YYYY-MM-DD-<change-name>`\n\n   **Check if target already exists:**\n   - If yes: Fail with error, suggest renaming existing archive or using different date\n   - If no: Move `changeRoot` to the archive directory\n\n   ```bash\n   mv \"<changeRoot>\" \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>\"\n   ```\n\n6. **Display summary**\n\n   Show archive completion summary including:\n   - Change name\n   - Schema that was used\n   - Archive location\n   - Whether specs were synced (if applicable)\n   - Note about any warnings (incomplete artifacts/tasks)\n\n**Output On Success**\n\n```\n## Archive Complete\n\n**Change:** <change-name>\n**Schema:** <schema-name>\n**Archived to:** the archive path derived from `planningHome.changesDir`/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>/\n**Specs:** ✓ Synced to main specs (or \"No delta specs\" or \"Sync skipped\")\n\nAll artifacts complete. All tasks complete.\n```\n\n**Guardrails**\n- Always prompt for change selection if not provided\n- Use artifact graph (openspec status --json) for completion checking\n- Don't block archive on warnings - just inform and confirm\n- Preserve .openspec.yaml when moving to archive (it moves with the directory)\n- Show clear summary of what happened\n- If sync is requested, use openspec-sync-specs approach (agent-driven)\n- If delta specs exist, always run the sync assessment and show the combined summary before prompting",
      "skill_otimizada": "---\nname: openspec-archive-change\ndescription: Archive a completed change safely. Use when the user wants to finalize and archive a unit of work after implementation.\nlicense: MIT\ncompatibility: Requires openspec CLI.\nmetadata:\n  author: openspec\n  version: \"2.0\"\n  generatedBy: \"1.4.1\"\n---\n\n# Archive Completed Work\n\nFinalize and archive a completed unit of work with full traceability.\n\n## Governing Principles\n\n> These principles override any specific step. When in doubt, apply the principle.\n\n1. **Explicit over implicit** — never guess the target; always let the user choose\n2. **Verify, don't block** — surface incomplete items as warnings, confirm intent, then proceed\n3. **Sync before seal** — if deltas exist against canonical state, assess and offer sync\n4. **Fail loudly on conflict** — collisions in archive destination are hard errors, not silent overwrites\n5. **Report transparently** — always end with a clear summary of actions taken and warnings encountered\n\n## Trigger\n\nUser requests archiving/finalizing a change. Optionally, a change name is provided.\n\n## Phase 1 — Target Resolution\n\n**Goal:** Unambiguously identify what to archive.\n\n| Situation | Action |\n|---|---|\n| Name provided explicitly | Proceed to Phase 2 |\n| Name inferable from active context | Proceed to Phase 2 |\n| Ambiguous or unspecified | List available (non-archived) changes via `openspec list --json` and **MUST** prompt user to select |\n\n**Implementation note:** Use the **AskUserQuestion tool** for selection. Show active changes only, include schema info if available. Never auto-select.\n\n## Phase 2 — Pre-Flight Verification\n\n**Goal:** Assess readiness across all dimensions; warn but do not block.\n\n### 2a. Scope Compatibility\nRun `openspec status --change \"<name>\" --json`.\n\nIf `actionContext.mode` indicates a workspace-level planning scope: **explain that workspace archiving is unsupported and STOP.** Do not relocate workspace-bound changes into repo-local archives.\n\n### 2b. Artifact Completeness\nParse status JSON for artifact states.\n\n- Any artifact not `done` → **warn** listing incomplete artifacts → confirm intent → proceed if confirmed\n\n### 2c. Task Completeness\nLocate task tracking (typically `tasks.md` within `changeRoot`).\n\n- Incomplete tasks found (`- [ ]` markers) → **warn** with count → confirm intent → proceed if confirmed\n- No task file found → proceed without warning\n\n**Unified confirmation:** If multiple warnings arise across 2b and 2c, present them as a single consolidated confirmation prompt rather than sequential interruptions.\n\n## Phase 3 — Delta Sync Assessment\n\n**Goal:** Determine if the change carries uncommitted deltas against canonical specs.\n\n**Check:** Use `artifactPaths.specs.existingOutputPaths` from status JSON to find delta specs.\n\n| Scenario | Action |\n|---|---|\n| No delta specs exist | Skip to Phase 4 |\n| Deltas exist | Compare each against corresponding canonical spec at `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md` |\n\n**If deltas exist, you MUST:**\n1. Categorize pending changes (adds, modifications, removals, renames)\n2. Present a **combined summary** of all deltas\n3. Prompt user with options:\n   - Changes pending → \"Sync now (recommended)\" / \"Archive without syncing\"\n   - Already synced → \"Archive now\" / \"Sync anyway\" / \"Cancel\"\n\n**If user chooses sync:** Delegate via **Task tool** (`subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"`) invoking `openspec-sync-specs` with the delta analysis embedded in the prompt. Then proceed to archive regardless.\n\n## Phase 4 — Archive Operation\n\n**Goal:** Atomically relocate the change to a dated archive folder.\n\n1. Ensure archive directory exists:\n   ```bash\n   mkdir -p \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive\"\n   ```\n2. Compute target path: `<planningHome.changesDir>/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>`\n3. **Collision guard:** If target path already exists → **fail with error** suggesting rename or alternate date\n4. Execute relocation:\n   ```bash\n   mv \"<changeRoot>\" \"<planningHome.changesDir>/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>\"\n   ```\n\n## Phase 5 — Summary\n\nReport archive outcome:\n\n```\n## Archive Complete\n\n**Change:** <change-name>\n**Schema:** <schema-name>\n**Archived to:** <planningHome.changesDir>/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<name>/\n**Specs:** ✓ Synced | Skipped | No delta specs\n**Warnings:** <count> (incomplete artifacts/tasks, if any)\n```\n\n## Decision Heuristics\n\n- **\"Should I ask?\"** → If there is any uncertainty about target, scope, or intent, the answer is always yes.\n- **\"Should I block?\"** → Only for hard conflicts (archive collision, unsupported scope). Incomplete items are warnings, not blockers.\n- **\"Should I sync?\"** → Only if deltas exist. Always show the combined summary before prompting. Let the user decide.\n- **\"Should I report?\"** → Always. Even when nothing unusual happened.",
      "regras_adicionais": "Preservar todas as regras comportamentais anteriores.",
      "manteve_regras_criticas": "True",
      "nota_clareza": "98",
      "nota_formatacao": "99",
      "nota_robustez": "96",
      "nota_densidade_informacional": "97",
      "nota_acionabilidade": "98",
      "nota_anti_fragilidade": "95",
      "feedback_detalhado": "A skill otimizada apresenta uma melhoria estrutural e cognitiva excepcional em relação à original. \n\n**Pontos Fortes:**\n1. **Arquitetura em Fases (Clareza e Acionabilidade):** A divisão em 5 fases distintas com objetivos explícitos elimina a linearidade amassada do original. Um agente de IA processa muito melhor as instruções quando elas têm escopo delimitado (\"Goal: Unambiguously identify what to archive\").\n2. **Tabelas de Decisão (Densidade e Formatação):** O uso de tabelas emestrutura mapeamento de estado-ação (ex: \"Situation | Action\" na Fase 1 e Fase 3) reduz drasticamente o ruído e ambiguidades. É uma forma perfeita de alta densidade informacional.\n3. **Heurísticas e Princípios (Anti-fragilidade e Robustez):** A adição de \"Governing Principles\" e \"Decision Heuristics\" no início e fim blinda o agente contra \"edge cases\". Se o agente esquecer uma regra gramatical, ele lembrará do princípio de \"Falhar alto em conflitos\" ou \"Verificar, não bloquear\".\n4. **Consolidação de Avisos:** A introdução da instrução de agrupar confirmações de tarefas e artefatos incompletos (em vez de perguntar duas vezes seguidas) demonstra um entendimento profundo de UX conversacional para agentes.\n\n**Pontos de Atenção (Minoritários):**\n1. O original tinha uma instrução explícita nos *Guardrails*: \"Preserve .openspec.yaml when moving to archive (it moves with the directory)\". A versão otimizada removeu essa nota textual, embora o comando `mv \"<changeRoot>\"` garanta isso estruturalmente na prática. Não compromete a execução, mas a menção literal sumiu.\n2. A instrução de exibir o \"schema usado\" para cada alteração na seleção inicial foi levemente resumida para \"include schema info if available\", mas mantém a semântica necessária.\n\n**Conclusão:**\nA otimização cumpre com excelência a regra adicional de \"Preservar todas as regras comportamentais anteriores\", traduzindo-as de uma lista chatamente sequencial para um sistema robusto orientado a princípios e fases. É significativamente mais imune a alucinações e perda de contexto."
    }
  ],
  "signature": {
    "instructions": "Avalia se uma skill otimizada para agentes de IA é estruturalmente superior à original.\nAnalisa 6 dimensões ortogonais: clareza, formatação, robustez, densidade informacional,\nacionabilidade e anti-fragilidade. Todas as regras exigidas devem ser cumpridas.",
